flowRoot.flowPara: Files is requesting to be able to change the background image. Granting permission will allow it to change the background and lock screen image at any time.
Allows an app to change the background whenever it wants. The main use case for this is apps that want to dynamically update the background, such as with a daily slideshow.
Allows an app to set an image as the desktop and/or lock screen background.
TODO: error handling, when the image is the wrong size or format. Possibly allow cropping an image whose aspect ratio is very different from the display's. But oh, what about screens that rotate...?
When a switch is on, the corresponding thumbnail shows the image that will be applied. When a switch is off, the current background image is shown.
When both switches are off, the set button should be insensitive.
